HEADWORD: Malacozoa
<hw>Mal`a*co*zo"a</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[NL.,
fr. Gr. <grk>malako`s</grk> soft + <grk>zw^,on</grk> an animal.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>An extensive group of Invertebrata, including
the <phylum>Mollusca</phylum>, Brachiopoda, and Bryozoa. Called also
<altname>Malacozoaria</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

